In recent times, thousands of Australian women have flocked to Thailand in for cut-price cosmetic surgery packages each year.

Dr Shaun Rudd, from the Australian Medical Association's Queensland branch, told local newspaper the Gold Coast Bulletin he could not support the event.

'Quality and safety are very important aspects of any work we do and to somehow trivialise these procedures doesn't sound like an appropriate thing to do,' Dr Rudd was quoted saying.

